<TITLE> Italy coach Donadoni's future to be set after Euro 2008 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ROME, March 21 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A decision Roberto Donadoni's future as Italy coach will not be made until after Euro 2008, the Italian Soccer Federation (FIGC) announced on Thursday. "The contractual relationship between Donadoni and the FIGC will be discussed again at its natural expiry in July," said the FIGC's Web site (www.figc.it). Earlier this month, the FIGC had said an agreement with Donadoni would be reached before next Wednesday's friendly with Spain. In February, Donadoni hinted he would be unhappy if a new deal was linked to the world champions' performance at Euro 2008 in Austria and Switzerland in June. But media reports said that FIGC President Giancarlo Abete was unwilling to offer an unconditional extension. "President Abete and Roberto Donadoni want to reiterate that they have a relationship of reciprocal faith and esteem on the professional and personal level that goes beyond contractual issues," said the FIGC statement. "They agree on a choice that will not remove the climate of serenity and responsibility that Roberto Donadoni has been able to guarantee the national team since his first day as Azzurri co
